AFM_plot
========

Having the spectroscopies of a AFM in a set of directories called
'grid_point_X' containing all the POSCAR.nn, CONTCAR,nn and OUTCAR,nn files, 
recursively gathers the information to generate the plots EvsZ, FvsZ, Delta_W
vs Z and generates the geoemetry .xyz file of every spectroscopy, ready to be
opened with Jmol (as coment line is  a Jmols script).

INPUT: inp.afm containing any of the input keywords
OUTPUT: 

Keywords for the inp.afm file:
------------------------------

Mandatory keywords
..................
- grid_points <int> <int> <int> ... ::  Number of the grid points to be plotted

Optional keywords
.................
- smoothing <float> :: Spline smoothinf factor
- z_min <float> :: minimum z value to do the E fitting
- z_max <float> :: maximum z value to do the E fitting
- datfile <str> :: Data filename wich includes E vs Z data values OUTCAR.X names
- tip_name <str> :: Name of the tip
- add_labels <bool> ::  If to add labels to the graphs 
- label_interval <int> :: Add label at every 'label_interval' step
- prefix <str> ::  Prefix for every output plot
- show_graphs <bool> :: If to show the graphs before saving them 
